    "7679082": {
      "title": "A primer on stochastic differential geometry for signal processing",
      "abstract": "This primer explains how continuous-time stochastic processes (precisely, Brownian motion and other Ito diffusions) can be defined and studied on manifolds. No knowledge is assumed of either differential geometry or continuous-time processes. The arguably dry approach is avoided of first introducing differential geometry and only then introducing stochastic processes; both areas are motivated and developed jointly."
    },
